hands_on_practices.solution:
The effective collision frequency is defined by
$$
\langle\nu_{ei}\rangle_{\text{eff}}
=\frac{\displaystyle\int f_M(v)\,v_{||}^2\,\nu_{ei}(v)\,d^3v}
{\displaystyle\int f_M(v)\,v_{||}^2\,d^3v}\,,
$$
with $\nu_{ei}(v)=\nu_0\,(v/v_{Te})^{-\alpha}= \nu_0\,v^{-\alpha}v_{Te}^{\alpha}$. Because $f_M$ is isotropic and $v_{||}^2=\frac{1}{3}v^2$, the angular integrals cancel in numerator and denominator, giving
$$
\langle\nu_{ei}\rangle_{\text{eff}}
=\nu_0\,v_{Te}^{\alpha}\,
\frac{\int_0^\infty v^{4-\alpha}e^{-b v^2}\,dv}
{\int_0^\infty v^4e^{-b v^2}\,dv},
\quad \text{where } b=\frac{m_e}{2T_e}\,.
$$
Using 
$$
\int_0^\infty v^n e^{-b v^2}dv
=\frac{1}{2}b^{-\frac{n+1}{2}}\Gamma\left(\frac{n+1}{2}\right),
$$
we find
$$
\langle\nu_{ei}\rangle_{\text{eff}}
=\nu_0\,v_{Te}^{\alpha}\,
\frac{\frac12b^{-\frac{5-\alpha}{2}}\Gamma\left(\frac{5-\alpha}{2}\right)}
{\frac12b^{-\frac{5}{2}}\Gamma\left(\frac{5}{2}\right)}
=\nu_0\,\frac{\Gamma\left(\frac{5-\alpha}{2}\right)}{\Gamma\left(\frac{5}{2}\right)},
$$
since $b=v_{Te}^{-2}$. In the banana regime $J_{bs}\propto 1/\langle\nu_{ei}\rangle_{\text{eff}}$, so
$$
\frac{J_{bs}(\alpha)}{J_{bs}(3)}
=\frac{\langle\nu_{ei}\rangle_{\text{eff}}(3)}
{\langle\nu_{ei}\rangle_{\text{eff}}(\alpha)}
=\frac{\Gamma\left(\frac{5-3}{2}\right)}{\Gamma\left(\frac{5-\alpha}{2}\right)}
=\frac{\Gamma(1)}{\Gamma\left(\frac{5-\alpha}{2}\right)}
=\frac{1}{\Gamma\left(\frac{5-\alpha}{2}\right)}\,. 
$$
